<title>USA: Smith Corona says court hearing set.</title>
<headline>Smith Corona says court hearing set.</headline>
<dateline>CORTLAND, N.Y. 1996-12-30</dateline>
<text>
<p>Smith Corona Corp said Monday that a hearing to confirm its bankruptcy reorganization plan has been scheduled for January 22.</p>
<p>The hearing is to be held at 2 p.m./1900 GMT in bankruptcy court in Wilmington, Del. Smith Corona said it believes the plan will be confirmed by the court.</p>
<p>Smith Corona, a manufacturer and marketer of personal word processors and typewriters, filed for Chapter 11 bankruptcy in July 1995.</p>
